  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Investigation of the incidence of endocrine dysfunction following subarachnoid hemorrhage
      (SAH), and to see if this has a relation to CNS lesions as evaluated by MRI and to common
      symptoms after SAH such as general exhaustion, lack of initiative, increased sleep demand and
      reduced quality of life.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
